Package edu.ncsu.csc216.business.model.stakeholders

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Landlord
    Landlord describes behaviors that the back end (model) must support for a front end (user interface) of the Wolf High-Rise Rental Application.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Client
    Creates a client object of name and id, There are other methods that are related to the client and lease classes such as add new lease, list lease, cancel lease and cancel lease with a specific confirmation number.
    PropertyManager
    This class follows the Singleton pattern which is "implemented through a private constructor and the method ProjectManager.getInstance(), which returns the only instance of ProjectManager." and the factory pattern which is "implemented through the method ProjectManager.addNewUnit() and the RentalUnit class hierarchy.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DuplicateClientException
    DuplicateClientException class when there are duplicate clients
    DuplicateRoomException
    DuplicateRoomException class when there are duplicate rooms
